            "text": "Different from traditional active learning ",
            "relation": "CONTRAST"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "based on sentence-wise full annotation ( FA ) , ",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "this paper proposes active learning with dependency-wise partial annotation ( PA ) as a finer-grained unit for dependency parsing . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "At each iteration , we select a few most uncertain words from an unlabeled data pool , ",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "manually annotate their syntactic heads , ",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "and add the partial trees into labeled data for parser retraining . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "Compared with sentence-wise FA , ",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "dependency-wise PA gives us more flexibility in task selection ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "and avoids wasting time on annotating trivial tasks in a sentence . <S>",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "Our work makes the following contributions . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "First , we are the first to apply a probabilistic model to active learning for dependency parsing , ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "which can 1 ) provide tree probabilities and dependency marginal probabilities as principled uncertainty metrics , ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "and 2 ) directly learn parameters from PA ",
            "relation": "JOINT"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "based on a forest-based training objective . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "Second , we propose and compare several uncertainty metrics through simulation experiments on both Chinese and English . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "Finally , we conduct human annotation experiments ",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
